title: JIP’s Ali Waqas wins PP-232 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 09 (APP): Ali Waqas of Jamaat-i-Islami Pakistan (JIP) has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-232, Vehari-IV by securing 26,206 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Abdul Waheed, an independent candidate who bagged 23,551 votes.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 56.31percent.
